00:00:06,260 --> 00:00:08,730
<i>Why am I...</i>

3
00:00:09,940 --> 00:00:12,650
<i>doing something like this?</i>

4
00:00:14,980 --> 00:00:19,120
<i>Where exactly... did my life go wrong?</i>

5
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:23,270
<i>[Two Months Ago]</i>

6
00:00:25,690 --> 00:00:27,920
<i>[Juntaku]</i>

7
00:00:33,980 --> 00:00:37,460
<i>[Juntaku: The Affluent Ale]</i>

8
00:00:37,460 --> 00:00:41,250
"Gift yourself an affluent tomorrow."

9
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:46,270
Soothe yourself after a hard day's work to get motivated for tomorrow.

10
00:00:46,290 --> 00:00:50,750
This "Juntaku" is a special beer, meant to evoke such visions.

11
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:52,380
Advertising Director,

12
00:00:52,380 --> 00:00:56,980
I hear you've proposed that a fifty-year-old male be cast in our commercial.

13
00:00:56,980 --> 00:01:00,840
The frugal youth aren't our target for luxury beers-

14
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:07,460
That is precisely why we must attract the non-beer-drinking youth.

15
00:01:10,810 --> 00:01:15,490
Does everyone here truly wish to revitalize the market?

16
00:01:15,490 --> 00:01:18,690
If we cannot propose new value here,

17
00:01:18,690 --> 00:01:21,630
our market has no future.

18
00:01:21,630 --> 00:01:23,440
As expected of Shitara-san.

19
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:25,280
He really silenced those directors.

20
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:28,500
His three President's Awards aren't only for show.

21
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:32,800
Rumors say his wife is a businesswoman who excels at housework too.

22
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:36,670
I beg the sales department to brainstorm new ideas for their respective fields.

23
00:01:36,670 --> 00:01:38,740
This concludes my presentation.

24
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:45,820
A transfer to Kazuki Systems?

25
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:49,000
Why?

26
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,720
I am the one who led the "Juntaku" project.

27
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,880
It's even set to be released in a month.

28
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,870
Why transfer me at such a crucial time?

29
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:59,940
Because your methods were deemed problematic.

30
00:01:59,940 --> 00:02:00,980
Pardon?

31
00:02:00,980 --> 00:02:05,700
Shitara, you forcibly acquired the Kanto manufacturing factory, didn't you?

32
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:08,530
That sent Executive Director Katou into a frenzy.

33
00:02:08,530 --> 00:02:10,530
But, Sir, that was my only option at the time-

34
00:02:10,530 --> 00:02:15,710
Still, the directors thought you were merely showing off.

35
00:02:16,780 --> 00:02:21,480
What will happen to the "Juntaku" project after my transfer?

36
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:24,270
It will be assigned to someone else.

37
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:28,040
Unfortunately, the decision is final.

38
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,180
<i>Me?</i>

39
00:02:34,820 --> 00:02:36,510
<i>Why?</i>

40
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,470
Hey!

41
00:02:41,390 --> 00:02:43,840
Wait, wait, wait!

42
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:46,420
I heard the Director summoned you. What for?

43
00:02:46,420 --> 00:02:49,900
Was it about the transfer to Kazuki Systems?

44
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,780
I knew it. Who is going from Product Development?

45
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:54,560
I hope they keep me in Sales.

46
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:58,660
Otherwise, I'm in trouble. That place is closing next year!

47
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:00,050
"Closing"?

48
00:03:00,050 --> 00:03:04,770
Exactly. In other words, this transfer is basically a layoff.

49
00:03:04,770 --> 00:03:07,530
<i>"Basically a layoff"?</i>

50
00:03:07,530 --> 00:03:12,000
Gosh, I'm so worried. I just got a mortgage loan-

51
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,690
Oh?

52
00:03:13,690 --> 00:03:14,840
What?

53
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,940
Shitara?

54
00:03:15,940 --> 00:03:19,020
Shitara? Shitara? Shitara!

55
00:03:20,310 --> 00:03:22,240
<i>All right, fine.</i>

56
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,590
Great job, Shitara.

57
00:03:23,590 --> 00:03:27,630
<i>If that's how you want to play, I have my own plans.</i>

58
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:30,200
<i>[Letter of Resignation]</i>

59
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:34,090
<i>I'll leave this despicable company on my own.</i>

60
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:39,420
<i>What will Natsumi say?</i>

61
00:03:40,450 --> 00:03:45,020
<i>No, I'm sure she'll understand. Probably.</i>

62
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:48,220
I'm home.

63
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:53,550
Natsumi?

64
00:03:54,420 --> 00:03:56,510
Monaka?

65
00:04:02,420 --> 00:04:05,080
<i>The good air conditioner? Gone.</i>

66
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:07,060
<i>The audio set up? Gone.</i>

67
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:09,230
<i>Monaka, the cat?</i>

68
00:04:09,230 --> 00:04:10,940
<i>Also gone.</i>

69
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:26,060
<i>[I've had enough.]</i>

70
00:04:26,060 --> 00:04:31,070
"Our sex may have been the only thing I liked about you."

71
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:40,250
A divorce?
<i>[Divorce Papers]</i>

72
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:52,230
<i>To think someone like me</i>

73
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:56,510
<i>would lose both my job and family in a day.</i>

74
00:04:58,970 --> 00:05:03,320
<i>I really don't know what will happen in the future.</i>

75
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:11,230
Yes. I previously worked for Product Development at Kazuki Beer

76
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:13,560
and spearheaded the "Juntaku" project.

77
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:17,100
The reason I quit Kazuki Beer?

78
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:21,710
It was a... life choice I made for my future.

79
00:05:21,710 --> 00:05:23,960
No, well...

80
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:29,580
I resigned with career development in mind.

81
00:05:29,580 --> 00:05:32,520
<i>[Dolce Bar]</i>

82
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,270
Finally!

83
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:37,020
<i>[Unfortunately, we must decline your application.]</i>

84
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:39,420
What?
<i>[...decline...]</i>

85
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:41,940
Were you rejected again?

86
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:44,930
Seriously?

87
00:05:44,930 --> 00:05:48,960
Kou-chan, don't be too ambitious now that you're divorced and all.

88
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:52,490
The divorce is unrelated to this. Besides, aren't you a fellow divorcee?

89
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:55,310
I wasn't abandoned.

90
00:05:55,310 --> 00:05:57,650
I was set free.

91
00:05:57,650 --> 00:05:59,000
Kaito-kun, could you please?

92
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,950
- Semantics don't matter.
- Yes, Ma'am.

93
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:05,630
So? What now? Maintaining the high-rise life must be rough.

94
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:10,680
Honestly, it's giving me trouble.

95
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,650
Then I have a proposition.

96
00:06:12,650 --> 00:06:15,470
How about you sign a Lover's Contract?

97
00:06:15,470 --> 00:06:16,550
L-Lover?

98
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:19,060
Exactly. The opposite of a sugar daddy.
<i>(T/N: man supporting a girlfriend with cash or gifts in exchange for companionship)</i>

99
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:21,650
The girls who come in often tell me

100
00:06:21,650 --> 00:06:25,930
they want a boyfriend who'll do all the chores and pay all the bills.

101
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:28,250
Shall I introduce one to you?

102
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:32,030
I don't see any benefit in such a dubious relationship.

103
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:37,290
People crave human warmth when times get tough, right?

104
00:06:37,290 --> 00:06:40,140
Not everything has to be about love.

105
00:06:40,140 --> 00:06:41,880
You think so?

106
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:06,180
<i>From her start with "Mommy Shima's Dumplings," Shitara Shimako has produced one hit product after another.</i>

107
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:11,340
<i>Her enterprise, the Shitara Group, profits around 25 billion yen annually (~$185 million)</i>

108
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:14,850
<i>and is a prominent representative of food culture in Japan.</i>

109
00:07:14,850 --> 00:07:18,860
<i>When I suddenly lost my husband in an accident,</i>
<i>[Shitara Group CEO: Shitara Shimako]</i>

110
00:07:18,860 --> 00:07:23,540
<i>I was burdened with heavy debt and hit a low point in life.</i>
<i>[Shitara Group CEO: Shitara Shimako]</i>

111
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:27,360
<i>Back then, Mom cried every day.</i>

112
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:30,560
<i>At age ten, I believed I was the only one</i>

113
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:33,190
<i>who could support her.</i>

114
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:38,440
<i>However, instead of giving in to despair, she began working.</i>

115
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:43,310
<i>Once she discovered the joy of being needed by others,</i>

116
00:07:43,310 --> 00:07:46,580
<i>her face brightened by the day.</i>

117
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:53,560
<i>One day, she made dumplings by hand in order to promote the sauce. The result?</i>

118
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:56,560
- <i>I'm not here for the sauce. I'd like the dumplings!
- Me too!</i>

119
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:59,030
<i>They were such an unexpected hit,</i>

120
00:07:59,030 --> 00:08:01,810
<i>she commercialized her cooking.
[Mommy Shima's Dumplings]</i>

121
00:08:01,810 --> 00:08:04,190
<i>With her unforeseen business skills,</i>

122
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:06,630
<i>she began expanding her company nationwide</i>

123
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:09,790
<i>and climbed the ladder of success.</i>

124
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:12,070
<i>No.</i>

125
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:15,390
<i>I then decided that the best support I could give</i>

126
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:18,700
<i>was to be a child</i>

127
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:21,930
<i>who wouldn't get in Mom's way.</i>

128
00:08:21,930 --> 00:08:23,400
<i>Do diligent work</i>

129
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,690
<i>and be needed by plenty.</i>

130
00:08:27,620 --> 00:08:32,040
<i>That's what we call "The pride of an entrepreneur."</i>

131
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,040
<i>[Mom]</i>

132
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:05,840
<i>[Shitara Kouichi: Sorry. I'm in the middle of work.]</i>

133
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,930
You're working too much.

134
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:11,190
Goodness, who did he take after?

135
00:09:12,090 --> 00:09:14,620
CEO, it's time.

136
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:35,130
<i>[Nao: Good news. I found you a good job.]</i>

137
00:09:35,130 --> 00:09:38,600
A good job? That's really vague.

138
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:47,200
<i>[What sort of job is it?]</i>

139
00:09:50,010 --> 00:09:51,790
<i>[Flexible hours.]</i>

140
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:54,510
<i>[Job-searching is allowed.]</i>

141
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:58,910
"It's a live-in job where you do the cooking and cleaning."

142
00:09:58,910 --> 00:10:01,050
<i>Shall I introduce one to you?</i>

143
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:07,020
Is Sister Nao seriously trying to get me into a Lover's Contract?

144
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:09,540
No, it's not happening.

145
00:10:20,170 --> 00:10:24,540
<i>Is this... where I die?</i>

146
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:28,600
<i>Deceased at age 31.</i>

147
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:32,900
<i>My brilliant life has now reached "The End."</i>

148
00:10:37,310 --> 00:10:42,020
<i>She must be... the last woman I'll ever see.</i>

149
00:10:47,610 --> 00:10:50,230
<i>[Unexpected - Love Story in Maison Ginseiso]</i>

150
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:03,100
Wh-Where am I?

151
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:05,710
It's my room.

152
00:11:05,710 --> 00:11:12,170
You tripped over yourself trying to dodge my bicycle.

153
00:11:22,170 --> 00:11:24,310
I have an interview to attend.

154
00:11:24,930 --> 00:11:27,100
You're at the right address.

155
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:29,320
I brought you here since it was listed on your phone.

156
00:11:30,350 --> 00:11:31,040
Pardon?

157
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:36,210
<i>Does that mean... this woman will hire me to be her lover?</i>

158
00:11:37,710 --> 00:11:43,840
This job entails both cooking and cleaning while living here, right?

159
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,520
That's correct.

160
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:49,940
Does it include... nightly tasks as well?

161
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:51,440
Of course.

162
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,490
It's all part of the job.

163
00:11:54,570 --> 00:11:57,810
<i>H-Her gaze is too intense!</i>

164
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:02,340
<i>Oh no, does she like me?</i>

165
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:05,010
Hold on, please.

166
00:12:06,410 --> 00:12:11,260
Yes, after getting divorced and being alone, I've been lonely, too.

167
00:12:12,110 --> 00:12:16,610
I understand you must long for human touch, sleeping in such a shabby room.

168
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:21,400
However, that does not warrant being a sugar mommy.

169
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:25,030
Hiring a lover will only feel worthless.

170
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:29,810
Besides, I don't want to rely on anyone just yet.

171
00:12:29,810 --> 00:12:32,860
I'm sorry. I'll have to refuse this job.

172
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:35,890
But you must accept, or else I'm in trouble.

173
00:12:42,010 --> 00:12:43,940
Are you seriously okay with that?

174
00:12:43,940 --> 00:12:45,160
Yes.

175
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:52,450
Fine. I'll be direct instead.

176
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:57,280
I can't... make love to you!

177
00:13:14,790 --> 00:13:16,940
Being a boarding-house caretaker?

178
00:13:16,940 --> 00:13:19,940
Then what was that about a "Lover's Contract"?

179
00:13:19,940 --> 00:13:23,070
Oh my gosh, I was obviously joking!

180
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:26,300
That woman punched me!

181
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:28,070
Not even my parents have...

182
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:30,640
My aunt's the usual caretaker here,

183
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:33,490
but she was hospitalized last week after getting hurt.

184
00:13:33,490 --> 00:13:36,320
That's when I remembered your predicament.

185
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:38,110
Why me? Oh!

186
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:41,820
Oh, Suzu-chan,

187
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:44,480
welcome back. How was the Comiket?
<i>(T/N: Convention where artists sell self-published goods and books)</i>

188
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:49,210
I bought as much as my budget allowed. The crop was plentiful.

189
00:13:52,650 --> 00:13:56,600
Oh, him? He's our new caretaker.

190
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:59,510
Nao-san's ex-achiever, divorced, jobless, childhood friend?

191
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:00,710
Hey!

192
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:07,200
Incompetent as I am, I shall be in your care.

193
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:10,760
Wait, I haven't agreed yet...

194
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:14,390
Our residents are three women.

195
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:16,990
If you cook breakfast and dinner and also clean,

196
00:14:16,990 --> 00:14:20,730
then your rent, meals, and utilities are all free of charge.

197
00:14:20,730 --> 00:14:24,010
Do I have to do the chores in an all-girl house?

198
00:14:24,010 --> 00:14:25,890
Are you really going to complain?

199
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:28,680
A jobless man should be grateful for the free benefits.

200
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:30,310
There's no need to rub it in.

201
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:34,010
Well then, one of my part-timers needs me. See you.

202
00:14:34,010 --> 00:14:35,960
Hold on, I haven't agreed.

203
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,960
<i>Itsuka-chan!</i>

204
00:14:39,260 --> 00:14:41,740
What the heck?

205
00:14:50,540 --> 00:14:54,170
Come, I'll give you the grand tour.

206
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:04,120
<i>[Maison Ginseiso]</i>

207
00:15:04,810 --> 00:15:06,980
<i>This is so awkward.</i>

208
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:10,300
<i>Does it include... nightly tasks as well?</i>

209
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:12,960
<i>Of course. It's all part of the job.</i>

210
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:18,040
<i>"Nightly tasks" must have meant dinner.</i>

211
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,110
<i>Either way...</i>

212
00:15:19,110 --> 00:15:22,760
<i>I can't... make love to you!</i>

213
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:25,650
<i>Yes, this is too awkward.</i>

214
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:31,710
Apparently, this is where the caretaker lives.

215
00:15:35,850 --> 00:15:38,670
<i>I-It's cramped!</i>

216
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:44,330
Our rules aren't any different from other boarding houses:

217
00:15:44,330 --> 00:15:47,330
don't bring in outsiders,

218
00:15:47,330 --> 00:15:50,590
don't barge into other's rooms, and so on.

219
00:15:50,590 --> 00:15:53,460
By the way, none of the rooms have locks.

220
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:55,260
No locks?

221
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:57,660
Isn't that dangerous?

222
00:15:57,660 --> 00:16:02,060
Not at all. Nao-san, Suzu-chan and I all trust each other.

223
00:16:03,450 --> 00:16:04,850
But...

224
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:08,780
I wouldn't even want to.

225
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:16,680
This kitchen can be used by any resident.

226
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:20,090
When placing something in the fridge,

227
00:16:20,090 --> 00:16:22,350
always mark it with your name.

228
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:23,850
That's...

229
00:16:26,310 --> 00:16:28,190
This? Nao-san loves it.

230
00:16:28,190 --> 00:16:31,540
Apparently, it's really popular at the moment.
<i>[Juntaku]</i>

231
00:16:31,540 --> 00:16:33,630
<i>Soothe yourself after a hard day's work</i>

232
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:35,910
<i>to get motivated for tomorrow.</i>

233
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:38,110
<i>A transfer to Kazuki Systems?</i>

234
00:16:40,190 --> 00:16:42,740
She says it's free to take-

235
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:44,270
Right.

236
00:16:45,610 --> 00:16:47,230
I got the basic idea.

237
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:54,170
Is something the matter?

238
00:16:54,170 --> 00:16:55,560
It's nothing.

239
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,180
In that case,

240
00:16:58,980 --> 00:17:01,800
this is no time to be idle.

241
00:17:02,590 --> 00:17:04,680
You've got work to do.

242
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:06,340
What?

243
00:17:11,460 --> 00:17:15,520
Scrub that spot with more gusto, please.

244
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:24,180
If you don't hurry, you'll be late shopping for dinner.

245
00:17:24,180 --> 00:17:27,090
